<statement><div><p>
During a mathematics lesson, Grade 10 students were asked to classify the number
<alert><m>{45038}</m></alert>.
</p>

<p>
Which of the following statements are true? Select all that apply.


</p><ol marker="(1)">
<li>It is odd</li>
<li>It is prime</li>
<li>It is composite</li>
<li>It is even</li>
</ol>   </div></statement>
<solution><div><p><alert>Worked Solution</alert></p>

<p>Given the number: <alert><m>{45038}</m></alert></p>

<hr/>

<p><alert>1. Test if the number is even or odd</alert></p>

<p>
We check the last digit of the number.
</p>

<p>
The last digit is 8, which is even. Therefore, the number is <alert>even</alert>.
</p>

<hr/>

<p><alert>2. Test if the number is prime or composite</alert></p>

<p>
The number has a divisor other than 1 and itself, so it is <alert>composite</alert>.
</p>

<hr/>

<p>
Therefore, the correct classification of <alert><m>{45038}</m></alert> is:
</p>

<ul>
<li>It is even</li>
<li>It is composite</li>
</ul></div></solution>
